title: Six nabbed in Johor land scandal
text:
JOHOR BARU: At least six people have been arrested during investigations into massive land corruption in the state.
The investigations involved the conversion of land premiums at "discounted rates" causing the state government to incur millions of ringgit in losses.
It is learnt that Malaysian Anti-Corruption Commission officers seized at least 15 luxury cars, local and foreign currencies, and documents in a series of raids on Friday.
At least 45 bank accounts involving over RM15.5mil have been frozen.
All the suspects, aged 25 and 50, have been remanded to assist in investigations.
MACC deputy commissioner (operations) Datuk Azam Baki confirmed the arrests.
